To say that the golden ratio formula_9 is rational means that formula_9 is a fraction formula_31 where formula_27 and formula_33 are integers. We may take formula_31 to be in lowest terms and formula_27 and formula_33 to be positive. But if formula_31 is in lowest terms, then the identity labeled (☆) above says formula_38 is in still lower terms. That is a contradiction that follows from the assumption that formula_9 is rational.
#### By irrationality of formula_20.
Another short proof – perhaps more commonly known – of the irrationality of the golden ratio makes use of the closure of rational numbers under addition and multiplication. If formula_41 is rational, then formula_42 is also rational, which is a contradiction if it is already known that the square root of a non-square natural number is irrational.
